wfEgpDelete.name: wfEgpDelete
wfEgpDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter for determining whether or not EGP is configured on this slot.

wfEgpDisable.name: wfEgpDisable
wfEgpDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter for determining whether or not to startup EGP.

wfEgpInMsgs.name: wfEgpInMsgs
wfEgpInMsgs.description: The aggregate number of EGP messages received in the box without error. This is part of the EGP group in Mib2.

wfEgpInErrors.name: wfEgpInErrors
wfEgpInErrors.description: The total number of all EGP messages received in the box that had errors. This is part of the EGP group in Mib2.

wfEgpOutMsgs.name: wfEgpOutMsgs
wfEgpOutMsgs.description: The total number of EGP locally generated messages from the box. This is part of the EGP group in Mib2.

wfEgpOutErrors.name: wfEgpOutErrors
wfEgpOutErrors.description: The total number of locally generated EGP messages from the box that had errors. This is part of the EGP group in Mib2.

wfEgpLocalAs.name: wfEgpLocalAs
wfEgpLocalAs.description: The NIC-assigned decimal number that identifies the local autonomous system.

wfEgpNeighTable.name: wfEgpNeighTable
wfEgpNeighTable.description: The EGP Neighbor table contains information regarding this EGP router's EGP neighbors on a particular interface. This table follows the egpNeighTable exactly as specified in he EGP group in Mib 2.

wfEgpNeighEntry.name: wfEgpNeighEntry
wfEgpNeighEntry.description: An entry in the EGP Neighbor table

wfEgpNeighState.name: wfEgpNeighState
wfEgpNeighState.description: The EGP state of the local system with respect to this entry's EGP neighbor. Each EGP state is represented by a value that is one greater than the numerical value associated with said state in RFC 904.

wfEgpNeighAddr.name: wfEgpNeighAddr
wfEgpNeighAddr.description: The IP address of this entry's EGP neighbor.

wfEgpNeighAs.name: wfEgpNeighAs
wfEgpNeighAs.description: The NIC-assigned decimal number that identifies the remote autonomous system (AS) of this EGP peer. Zero should be specified if the AS number of the neighbor is not yet known.

wfEgpNeighInMsgs.name: wfEgpNeighInMsgs
wfEgpNeighInMsgs.description: The number of EGP messages received without error from this EGP peer.

wfEgpNeighInErrs.name: wfEgpNeighInErrs
wfEgpNeighInErrs.description: The number of EGP messages received from this EGP peer that proved to be in error (e.g., bad EGP checksum).

wfEgpNeighOutMsgs.name: wfEgpNeighOutMsgs
wfEgpNeighOutMsgs.description: The number of locally generated EGP messages to this EGP peer.

wfEgpNeighOutErrs.name: wfEgpNeighOutErrs
wfEgpNeighOutErrs.description: The number of locally generated EGP messages not sent to this EGP peer due to resource limitations within an EGP entity.

wfEgpNeighInErrMsgs.name: wfEgpNeighInErrMsgs
wfEgpNeighInErrMsgs.description: The number of EGP-defined error messages received from this EGP peer.

wfEgpNeighOutErrMsgs.name: wfEgpNeighOutErrMsgs
wfEgpNeighOutErrMsgs.description: The number of EGP-defined error messages sent to this EGP peer.

wfEgpNeighStateUps.name: wfEgpNeighStateUps
wfEgpNeighStateUps.description: The number of EGP state transitions to the UP state with this EGP peer.

wfEgpNeighStateDowns.name: wfEgpNeighStateDowns
wfEgpNeighStateDowns.description: The number of EGP state transitions from the UP state to any other state with this EGP peer.

wfEgpNeighIntervalHello.name: wfEgpNeighIntervalHello
wfEgpNeighIntervalHello.description: The interval between EGP Hello command retransmissions (in seconds). This represents the t1 timer as defined in RFC 904.

wfEgpNeighIntervalPoll.name: wfEgpNeighIntervalPoll
wfEgpNeighIntervalPoll.description: The interval between EGP poll command retransmissions (in seconds). This represents the t3 timer as defined in RFC 904.

wfEgpNeighMode.name: wfEgpNeighMode
wfEgpNeighMode.description: The polling mode of this EGP entity, either passive or active.

wfEgpNeighEvent.name: wfEgpNeighEvent
wfEgpNeighEvent.description: The EGP event that occurred on the local interface with respect to this entry's EGP neighbor.

wfEgpNeighBadAsns.name: wfEgpNeighBadAsns
wfEgpNeighBadAsns.description: The number of received EGP messages that contained an unrecognized AS number in the EGP header.

wfEgpNeighBadCodes.name: wfEgpNeighBadCodes
wfEgpNeighBadCodes.description: The number of received EGP messages that contained an unrecognized value in the Code field in the EGP header.

wfEgpNeighBadHellos.name: wfEgpNeighBadHellos
wfEgpNeighBadHellos.description: The number of unexpected Hello neighbor reachability messages received by EGP. A Hello message is unexpected when received from a passive peer.

wfEgpNeighBadIHUs.name: wfEgpNeighBadIHUs
wfEgpNeighBadIHUs.description: The number of unexpected I Hear You neighbor reachability messages received by EGP. A I Hear You message is unexpected when received in the absence of a prior Hello message.

wfEgpNeighBadStatuses.name: wfEgpNeighBadStatuses
wfEgpNeighBadStatuses.description: The number of received EGP messages that contained an unrecognized value in the Status field in the EGP header.

wfEgpNeighBadChecksums.name: wfEgpNeighBadChecksums
wfEgpNeighBadChecksums.description: The number of received EGP messages that contained a faulty checksum in the EGP header.

wfEgpNeighBadTypes.name: wfEgpNeighBadTypes
wfEgpNeighBadTypes.description: The number of received EGP messages that contained an unrecognized value in the Type field in the EGP header.

wfEgpNeighBadVersions.name: wfEgpNeighBadVersions
wfEgpNeighBadVersions.description: The number of received EGP messages that contained an invalid EGP Version number in the EGP header. This EGP implementation supports EGP Version 2.

wfEgpNeighCmdOutOfSeqs.name: wfEgpNeighCmdOutOfSeqs
wfEgpNeighCmdOutOfSeqs.description: The number of times EGP received an out-of-sequence command message. An out-of-sequence message indicates that a prior message, issued by an EGP peer, has been missed.

wfEgpNeighCmdRejects.name: wfEgpNeighCmdRejects
wfEgpNeighCmdRejects.description: The number of times EGP refused to respond to a received command. Such refusal could be generated by receipt of a neighbor acquisition message from an unknown AS, or by receipt of a faulty EGP message (for example, one with a bad checksum) from a known neighbor.

wfEgpCfgNeighTable.name: wfEgpCfgNeighTable
wfEgpCfgNeighTable.description: This table is used to configure the parameters for a relationship with a particular local EGP neighbor. This table is proprietary and not part of the standard EGP MIB.

wfEgpCfgNeighEntry.name: wfEgpCfgNeighEntry
wfEgpCfgNeighEntry.description: An entry in the EGP Cfg Neighbor table

wfEgpCfgNeighDelete.name: wfEgpCfgNeighDelete
wfEgpCfgNeighDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object to create/delete an EGP neighbor relationship with the specified local IP address.

wfEgpCfgNeighDisable.name: wfEgpCfgNeighDisable
wfEgpCfgNeighDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Users perforn an SNMP SET operation on this object to enable/disable an EGP Neighbor relationship with the specified local IP address. Default is enabled. This variable is also used to trigger operator-initiated Start and Stop events in the EGP FSM. It takes the place of the egpNeighEventTrigger variable. When set, this variable causes a Start or Stop event on the specified neighbor, as specified on pages 8-10 of RFC 904. Briefly, a Start event causes an Idle peer to begin neighbor acquisition and a non-Idle peer to reinitiate neighbor acquisition. A stop event causes a non-Idle peer to return to the Idle state until a Start event occurs, either via egpNeighEventTrigger or otherwise. This parameter is part of MIB 2. NOTE: The FSM is only affected if EGP is Enabled on the slot.

wfEgpCfgNeighState.name: wfEgpCfgNeighState
wfEgpCfgNeighState.description: This parameter relfects the current state of the specified EGP neighbor relationship with specfied local IP address.

wfEgpCfgNeighLocalAddr.name: wfEgpCfgNeighLocalAddr
wfEgpCfgNeighLocalAddr.description: The IP address of the local interface that provides the EGP connection to the remote autonomous system.

wfEgpCfgNeighRemoteAddr.name: wfEgpCfgNeighRemoteAddr
wfEgpCfgNeighRemoteAddr.description: The IP address of the remote interface that provides the EGP connection to the remote autonomous system.

wfEgpCfgNeighGatewayMode.name: wfEgpCfgNeighGatewayMode
wfEgpCfgNeighGatewayMode.description: This parameter specifies the EGP gateway mode of this IP interface. The two modes are core and non-core. When the interface is configured in non-core mode, it will advertise and forward only traffic that originated or is destined for a local network within its AS. When configured for this mode, certain EGP Export Route Filters are auto- matically configured for this interface. When the interface is configured in Core mode, it can advertise and forward traffic to networks interior or exterior to its local AS. The default is Core mode.

wfEgpCfgNeighAcqMode.name: wfEgpCfgNeighAcqMode
wfEgpCfgNeighAcqMode.description: This parameter specifies which of the two neighbors will initiate EGP connections. This configures the mode for the local EGP neighbor. Note: At least one neighbor must be in the Active mode.

wfEgpCfgNeighPollMode.name: wfEgpCfgNeighPollMode
wfEgpCfgNeighPollMode.description: This parameter specifies the type of neighbor reachability algorithm this local EGP neighbor will execute.

wfEgpCfgNeighHelloTimer.name: wfEgpCfgNeighHelloTimer
wfEgpCfgNeighHelloTimer.description: This parameter specifies the interval between EGP Hello command retransmissions (in seconds) by the local EGP neighbor. This represents the t1 timer as defined in RFC 904.

wfEgpCfgNeighPollTimer.name: wfEgpCfgNeighPollTimer
wfEgpCfgNeighPollTimer.description: This parameter specifies the interval between EGP poll command retransmissions (in hundredths of a second) by the local EGP neighbor. This represents the t3 timer as defined in RFC 904.
